@DATABASE "Thundercats"
@NODE "MAIN" "SPECCY POKES - T - Thundercats"
@TOC "MAIN"

                   ZX SPECTRUM (SPECCY heheh) POKES - T
                   ====================================

                                Thundercats
                                ===========



DESCRIPTION              POKE
===========              ====

@{"Infinite Lives" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(31403,24)"}          31403,24
@{"Infinite Time " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(25291,0)"}          25291,0
@{"Immunity      " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(32219,1)"}          32219,1
@{"No Enemies    " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(31474,201)"}          31474,201
@{"Weird 128 only" RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPoke(30060,0)"}          30060,0
@{"Lives = x     " RXS "ADDRESS COMMAND ZXAMPOKE(29228,99)"}          29228,x (x= 1-99)


                         Change x to whatever value you wish, using
                         the POKE option on the ZXAM GUI. Simply
                         click the button to get the maximum value
                         x can be (usually 255).


                         The "Lives = x" POKE was by me. I had done an
                         "Infinite Lives" POKE, but someone else had
                         done it.

                         Rastan.
@endnode
